The '''''Ambarnath Marathi Film Festival''''' (also known as '''AMFF''') ({{lang-mr|'''अंबरनाथ मराठी फिल्म फेस्टिवल'''}}) is held every year in the city of [[Ambarnath]], in the state of [[Maharashtra]] in [[India]]. Festival conducted by Akhil Bhartiya Marathi Chitrapat Mahamandal,<ref>'Loksatta (5 Nov 2017) ' 'http://epaper.loksatta.com/c/23450930'</ref><ref>'Pudhari' 'http://newspaper.pudhari.co.in/home.php?edition=Mumbai&date=-1&pageno=4&pid=PUDHARI_MUM#Article/PUDHARI_MUM_20171105_04_6/452px' {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171108151900/http://newspaper.pudhari.co.in/home.php?edition=Mumbai&date=-1&pageno=4&pid=PUDHARI_MUM#Article/PUDHARI_MUM_20171105_04_6/452px' |date=8 November 2017 }}</ref> and Ambar Bharari.<ref>[http://www.yuvamaharashtralive.com/2016/10/2016_5.html?m=0 Yuva Maharashtra]</ref><ref name=MT1 />
The festival has taken place annually in October–November since 2015.<ref>[http://www.lokmat.com/thane/marathi-film-festival-ambernath/ Lokmat Official News]</ref> Festival allows entry to Release - Unreleased [[marathi film]], short-film's of year. The festival is arranged by Ambar Bharari President Sunil Chaudhari, Nikhil Chaudhari and President of Akhil Bhartiya Marathi Chitrapat Mahamandal. [[Mahendra Patil]] is the Director of the festival.<ref>[http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/ambarnath-marathi-film-festival-to-be-held-from-oct-30-nov-2/1/499296.html, India Today - PTI News Feed]</ref> Third film festival has been held in Sept - Oct 2017 in which 30 films and 50 Short films has been screened. Award Ceremony is scheduled on 26 November 2017.,<ref>'Loksatta (5 Nov 2017) ' 'http://epaper.loksatta.com/c/23450930'</ref><ref>'Pudhari' 'http://newspaper.pudhari.co.in/home.php?edition=Mumbai&date=-1&pageno=4&pid=PUDHARI_MUM#Article/PUDHARI_MUM_20171105_04_6/452px' {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171108151900/http://newspaper.pudhari.co.in/home.php?edition=Mumbai&date=-1&pageno=4&pid=PUDHARI_MUM#Article/PUDHARI_MUM_20171105_04_6/452px' |date=8 November 2017 }}</ref>
== Awards == Ambarnath Film Festival has 35 different category awards for films, 10 categories for short-films,<ref>[https://www.mahanews.gov.in/Home/HomeDetails.aspx?str=vj9+kFu2lFY= AMFF Awards, MahaNews Official Website]</ref><ref>[http://www.loksatta.com/manoranjan-news/in-ambarnath-film-festival-film-walya-to-walmiki-got-good-responce-1340660/ Loksatta]</ref>
