'''Emil Hermann Zeck''' (16 November 1891 – 3 September 1963) was an Australian [[entomology|entomologist]] and biological illustrator. He was highly respected for his beautiful and scientifically accurate illustrations, especially of insects.

==Life==
Zeck was born in Sydney. His artistic talent was recognised early and from 1908 to 1923 he worked as an entomological [[Technical illustration|illustrator]] at the Government Printing Office in Sydney. He subsequently joined the staff of the [[Department of Primary Industries (New South Wales)|New South Wales Department of Agriculture]] as an entomologist and remained there until his retirement in 1956.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.eoas.info/biogs/P001954b.htm |title= Zeck, Emil Hermann (1891 - 1963) |accessdate=2014-04-28 |work= |first=GJ |last=McCarthy |publisher= Encyclopedia of Australian Science |date=2004-09-15 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.dpi.nsw.gov.au/aboutus/services/collections/scientific-illustrations/zeck |title= Paintings of insects by EH Zeck |accessdate=2014-04-28 |work= |first= |last= |publisher= NSW Dept of Primary Industries |date=}}</ref>

==Honours and awards==
* Fellow of the [[Royal Zoological Society of New South Wales]] (1951)
* [[Australian Natural History Medallion]] (1961)

